&gt; software components -- then first identify the area you are most
&gt; interested in testing: handling a request, building a response, data
&gt; access, selecting business logic, whatever. Next, try writing a JUnit
&gt; test that uses JUST THAT PORTION of your server application. If you
&gt; find that you can&#39;t do that without involving other pieces of the
&gt; application, then you have some dependency splitting to do. Divide and
&gt; conquer, divide and conquer.
